The paper presents a new data structure for graph processing in the graph-streaming setting, which involves continuous updates to a graph mixed with arbitrary queries. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) category. Additionally, the paper focuses on compressing the data structure to improve space usage and locality, which suggests that it may also belong to the Databases (cs.DB) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) categories. The paper also discusses batch updates and efficient algorithms, which suggests that it may belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of a single commodity multicore server, which suggests that it may also belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category.
